    import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import matplotlib.colors as mcolors import mpl_toolkits.mplot3d.axes3d as axes3d from matplotlib import cm %matplotlib inline
    • Distributions:
    $$ D_o(\omega_o(x_o, y_o, z_o)) $$
    • These distributions blow are all normalized:
    $$ \int_{\Omega} D_o(\omega_o) \mathrm{d} \omega_o = 1 $$
    In [2]:
    Copied! 
    def spherical_plot(pdf, title):
    COUNT = 200
    Theta, Phi = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, COUNT), np.linspace(0, np.pi, COUNT)
    dist = np.zeros((COUNT,COUNT))
    
    # values
    for j, theta in enumerate(Theta):
        for i,phi in enumerate(Phi):
            x = np.sin(phi)*np.cos(theta)
            y = np.sin(phi)*np.sin(theta)
            z = np.cos(phi)
            dist[i][j] = pdf([x,y,z])

    # mesh grid
    THETA, PHI = np.meshgrid(Theta, Phi)
    X = np.sin(PHI) * np.cos(THETA)
    Y = np.sin(PHI) * np.sin(THETA)
    Z = np.cos(PHI)
    
    # face colors
    coolwarm = plt.get_cmap('coolwarm')
    norm = mcolors.Normalize(vmin=dist.min(), vmax=dist.max())
    fcolors = coolwarm(norm(dist))

    # plot
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=[10,10])
    ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1, projection='3d')
    
    ax.plot_surface(X, Y, Z, rstride=1, cstride=1, cmap=coolwarm, facecolors=fcolors,
        linewidth=0, antialiased=False)

    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

    Uniform Spherical Distribution¶

    $$ D_o = \frac{1}{4 \pi} $$

    return 1/(4*np.pi)
    def do_uniform_sphere(w): return 1/(4*np.pi)

    Uniform Hemispherical Distribution¶

    $$ D_{o}(\omega_{o})= \begin{cases} \frac{1}{2 \pi} & \text { if } \quad z_o \geq 0 \\ 0 & \text { if } \quad z_o<0 \end{cases} $$
    In [5]:
    Copied! 
    def do_uniform_hemisphere(w):
    if w[2]<0:
        return 0
    else:
        return 1 / (2*np.pi)
    def do_uniform_hemisphere(w): if w[2]<0: return 0 else: return 1 / (2*np.pi)
    In [6]:
    Copied! 
    spherical_plot(do_uniform_hemisphere,'Uniform Hemispherical Distribution')
    spherical_plot(do_uniform_hemisphere,'Uniform Hemispherical Distribution')

    Clamped Cosine Distribution¶

    $$ D_o(\omega_o)= \begin{cases} \frac{z_o}{\pi} & \text{ if } \quad z_o \geq 0 \\ 0 & \text{ if } \quad z_o<0 \end{cases} $$
    • RecallSpherical Coordinates V.S. Cartesian Coordinate
    $$ \begin{align} x =& \rho \sin(\phi) \cos(\theta) \\ y =& \rho \sin(\phi) \sin(\theta) \\ z =& \rho \cos(\phi) \end{align} $$
    In [7]:
    Copied! 
    def do_clamped_cosine(w):
    return np.maximum(0, w[2]/np.pi)
    def do_clamped_cosine(w): return np.maximum(0, w[2]/np.pi)
    In [8]:
    Copied! 
    spherical_plot(do_clamped_cosine,'Clamped Cosine Distribution')
    spherical_plot(do_clamped_cosine,'Clamped Cosine Distribution')

    Squared Clamped Cosine Distribution¶

    $$ D_o(\omega_o)= \begin{cases} \frac{3 z_o^2}{2 \pi} & \text{ if } \quad z_o \geq 0 \\ 0 & \text{ if } \quad z_o<0 \end{cases} $$
    In [9]:
    Copied! 
    def do_squared_clamped_cosine(w):
    return np.maximum(0, w[2]**2*3 / (2*np.pi))
    def do_squared_clamped_cosine(w): return np.maximum(0, w[2]**2*3 / (2*np.pi))
